# Intake — AdvertEyes

## Brief summary
**AdvertEyes**: OOH advertising company (billboards, truckside wraps, digital DOOH screens). Internal business platform (not SaaS) for operations, inventory management, campaign coordination, and user/role management. Feature richness 10/10; full production-quality build.

## Hero feature
**Campaign Operations Dashboard** — multi-view module combining:
- Inventory (billboards, trucks, DOOH screens) with location, size, type, availability, rate
- Clients/advertisers, campaigns (flights with dates, budget, assigned inventory)
- Bookings linking campaigns to inventory with conflict detection
- RBAC (Admin, Sales, Ops/Installer, Client-viewer) gating views/operations
- KPI tiles, filterable reports/tables, dashboard views

## Supporting features
1. **Weather & Install-Risk** — Open-Meteo API (free, no key) shows current + forecast by location. Flags install risk (rain/high-wind halts vinyl installs). Domain-credible integration (weather drives OOH dayparting, scheduling, impression estimates).
2. **User & Role Management** — Demo login seeded per role; protected routes; token-based auth; RBAC enforcement.

## Tech stack (from posting + Michael's directive)
- **Frontend:** React + TypeScript + Vite; build to `../michaelwegter.com/public/demos/adverteyes/`
- **Backend:** Node.js + Express.js + TypeScript; Surface runner → Flask bridge at `api.michaelwegter.com/adverteyes/...` (preferred); fallback: seeded frontend data + Open-Meteo called from browser
- **Database:** SQLite or JSON store for demo (seeded with inventory, campaigns, bookings, users)
- **API:** Open-Meteo (weather); internal REST APIs for inventory/campaigns/bookings/users

## Posting's mandatory "to apply" requirements (cover letter must address all)
1. Experience with custom web applications ← app architecture + implementation demo
2. Admin dashboards/internal tools built ← Campaign Ops Dashboard is the anchor
3. Strongest FE + BE stack ← React + TS, Node + Express + TS
4. API integration experience ← Open-Meteo + internal APIs
5. Availability this week ← demo is production-ready, day-one launchable

## Explicit posting requirements
- Custom web app features (inventory, campaigns, bookings, user mgmt)
- Clean, responsive frontend with forms, filters, tables, reports
- Admin dashboard functionality
- RBAC, authentication, protected routes
- Secure backend APIs, database-driven workflows
- Third-party API integration (Open-Meteo)
- Deployment-ready with clear documentation
- Full-stack ownership: FE UI + BE API architecture + DB structure

## Design direction (NOT portfolio's look)
Bold, visual, confident operations-tool aesthetic. High-contrast, map-forward, professional. Researcher to pull OOH industry cues (Lamar, Clear Channel, OUTFRONT); planner to lock palette, typography, mood. No em/en dashes anywhere.

## Acceptance gates (evaluator enforces)
- Dashboard builds, loads, no console errors
- All posting explicit requirements addressed in cover letter + demo
- Campaign Ops, weather integration, RBAC all functional
- Demo URL resolves locally; `/work-samples/adverteyes` returns 200 after deploy
- Node backend live and bridged; Open-Meteo responds
- Design is cohesive, bespoke, OOH-credible
- Demo link in cover letter + deck
- Zero em/en dashes

