- produced: brief.json (11 fields: hero, supporting, stack, tech, requirements, design, acceptance gates, URLs, registry id)
- decisions: full build (richness 10); Campaign Ops Dashboard hero; Open-Meteo weather/install-risk supporting; Node/Express backend via Surface runner (seeded-data fallback if flaky); RBAC with demo login per role
- next needs: planner to lock design system + hero/supporting boundary + backend implementation path (real Node service vs. seeded data fallback); researcher to pull OOH industry/competitor aesthetic cues
- risks: Surface Node/TS build may be flaky within budget (fallback documented); must keep to 1 hero + 2 supporting + ~12 demo files; no em/en dashes in any prose
